Alexandria
==========

    Alexandria is a GNOME application to manage one or more collections of
    books.  It features a user interface compliant with the HIG rules, and
    it retrieves information about books from Amazon, using its web service. 

Requirements
------------

    Ruby >= 1.8.0:          http://www.ruby-lang.org
    GNOME >= 2.x:           http://www.gnome.org
    Ruby-GNOME2 >= 0.9.x:   http://ruby-gnome2.sourceforge.jp
    Ruby/Amazon >= 0.7.x:   http://www.caliban.org/ruby/ruby-amazon.shtml

Install
-------

    $ ruby install.rb setup
    $ ruby install.rb config
   ($ su)
    $ ruby install.rb install

Usage
-----

    $ alexandria

